==English==

===Etymology===
{{unk|en}}; circa 1940s; thought to be a reference to [[Dear John letter]]s. Ernest Tubb recorded a song entitled ''That's All She Wrote'' (sheet music published in 1942), but earlier printed references exist (e.g. The Brownsville Herald, June 1935).

